annotation.TEXT: Well, anyway, the secret exit's route won, so let's go on over to 2-A! (Had I let the desynched footage play out entirely, you would've gotten a sneak peek earlier, but you wouldn't have seen anything spectacular-- Just the first screen of the level.)
Umm... Did I miss a star coin somewhere? Or is it on the other side of this pipe?
I forget why I was pressing a screen-scrolling button here...
Well, there's a goal... already? But, I only got two star coins, and didn't even see a midpoint... So, this must be the secret exit!
Ha! Block clone success!
However, I did use a bit of tool-assistance to make sure this bonus game played out exactly as it did the first time.
Also, wow, it's very unusual for me to play the bonus game twice in one video! Let's see if I can perfect it this time...
And there's a lone muncher there, probably so that players can suicide if they royally screw up this puzzle, perhaps by wasting all of the ice blocks. (What? No reset door or pipe here?)
Which one should I play next (after I'm done looking through 2-A for that star coin)? Place your votes now, and we'll find out next time!
Toasty!
Oh, nuts! Well, I hope that door I came from was a reset door! (It probably is.)

Okay, maybe I overhyped the epicness of that moment just a bit, but I really am glad that that moment wasn't stolen from me by ZSNES's desync. Why do desyncs like that occur anyway? Is the emulator not capable of properly recording my inputs 100% of the time?

Fortunately, this is where the desynched and reshot part ends, since I recorded each level on a separate movie file, so as soon as I return to the overworld here, I'm back to untainted footage. (Note: My score will differ slightly from what it is here, but lives, stars, and coins will be the same.)
That was a cool stomp there that didn't happen the first time. Now, I saw the pipe above, and eventually deduced that it must be the level's midpoint entrance.
Hmm... I wonder if there was an invisible block back there I could've used instead...
Well, let's see what happens...
Alright, we're back to when I first made the block factory here. And now, I'll try to perform mostly the same actions that I did before.
Huh. The ON/OFF switches briefly become footballs when I hit them. I guess they aren't in the best sprite tileset for this sort of thing.
Looks like I have to use at least one ice block here.
Okay, this time, ZSNES didn't desync when I successfully jumped off of the green blocks to get up here...
Hello, and welcome back to Super Marina World! Okay, so here I am in the Vanilla Dome-- Uh, I mean Salt Cavern, about to enter this level that most likely involves ON/OFF switches...
Demo count: 3?
Hmm... it appears that the terrain is completely solid to the right (possibly because of an upside-down ceiling object), so I can't break the level this way.
And fortunately, just like last time, the graphical glitch was only temporary. Now, let's go back for the normal exit.
Oh, she wants another go. But, this can only end badly...
Bonus game average so far: 38 / 5 = 7.6 1-ups each.
Demo count: 0

Alright, so now that that level is out of the way, I have two places I could go, the normal exit's route (2-3), and the secret exit's route (2-A). Let's take a look at those votes and see where I'm heading next!

Over here, I bounced off a Swooper to reach a star coin, but then figured that that might not have been the intended way to reach it. (The "proper" way likely involved hitting an ON/OFF block to the right and then coming back here.)
Oh, man. It's a Porcu-Puffer, and it's also toast!
Goal tape average so far: 460 / 12 = 38.333 stars each.
So, I accidentally glitched through the wall there to my doom, but then I managed to save myself with a quick shell jump! Wow!
Ah, but I had remembered seeing a star coin to the left, which I of course must have! So I made my way over to it, which wasn't too difficult.
I ditched Buzzy there, and then ended up performing a glitch a few times, being careful not to fall off the bottom of the level while doing so.
Huh? An invisible block? Maybe it's to help a player get over the pipe if they've fried all of the frozen blocks and the tide is low.
Okay, this is getting annoying...
Now, why in the world are all of these invisible blocks here? Is there an off screen secret up above?
I took another dumb hit from a Porcu-Puffer there, but there was a replacement flower immediately available that time.
I noticed the gap to the right of the door, and figured that might lead somewhere (with Start+Select on my side just in case my hunch was wrong).
I'm definitely thankful to encounter a goal now though, given how little time I had left.
BGM: Hexyz Force - Desperation
Goal tape average: 390 / 10 = 39 stars each.
Heh. Oddly, I think that Porcu-Puffer died from being near the block I broke, and not from being hit directly by my fire.
I highly doubt I'll need to worry about all those shells at the start now, but what were they for?
I love roasting fish with fireballs that magically work in water for some reason.
Well, this must be the path that was just created, and it leads to 2-A, so that was indeed the secret exit.
Yes!
Uh, oh. Looks like an escort mission! I bet I need to keep that parakoopa alive!
Umm, what? Not again... Are these glitchy-looking overworld paths going to become a thing with this hack?

Oh, and it turns out that this is indeed where the normal path continues! Also, if I had fallen for that trap, I would've just ended up down here instead of dying. (And this is where I had used the screen-scrolling buttons the first time, and yes, that koopa did die like that the first time as well.)
Goal tape average so far: 510 / 13 = 39.231 stars each.
Yeah, that's not a surprise.
Parakoopa demo count: 1

Yes, I did indeed get only 30 stars the first time too, and I would've used tool-assistance to make sure I got exactly 30 again on the reshoot here, but I naturally hit the 30 again on my first attempt.
And then I slide-killed a bunch of Buzzies, grabbed the last star coin, and hit the goal.
Well, there are a lot of frozen blocks here, but I'm not seeing any star coin... I must've missed it somewhere.
What, really?! I had to go and take a dumb hit like that just after mentioning that I wanted to hang onto my fire power? Ugh...
Oh, sweet! Well, at least something good came out of replaying this level!

Kind of like this. Now, while this may seem silly, if a player entered here fiery, it's completely understandable that the player may accidentally fry the shell, so it definitely makes sense for there to be a reset pipe.
Okay, now let's do this for realsies.
That definitely counts as an epic moment! However, why did I phase through the wall like that?
Just making sure I checked that pipe properly.
To be continued...
Oh, well. Let's move on, as I've wasted enough time. (Why do I tend to run low on time a lot? Maybe because I like to check for secrets everywhere?)
Now, here, after disarming this trap again, I was wondering where to go from here for the normal path. And then, it hit me that there must be some reason that door was two-way.
50-star hits: 2
Oh, man. Getting tricky!
Demo count: 2?
I'll take that as a "yes".
OH, MY GOD!!! We have got to see an instant replay of that!
I did a quick check to the left with the L button here just to make sure there was nothing over there.
Yep, that's exactly what happened the first time. I did indeed land a flower on the first panel there, screwing up my perfect bonus game streak and saddening me...
Bonus game average so far: 30 / 4 = 7.5 1-ups each.
Oh, it's because of a glitch due to the way the slope here meets a solid tile. If you land on the corner just right, you can walk right through.
This ON/OFF puzzle went just like this.
Oh, it must be a reset pipe, in case you destroy the shell you need to hit the ON/OFF switch.
Up next, this "maze". It's actually not very complicated either, and I navigated it pretty much like this.
"?"? What does "?" mean?
Moving along, I hit midpoint, and then proceeded to play around with this Buzzy and a steep slope (not exactly like this, but close enough).
In the meantime, the newly opened levels are: 2-B up there, and 2-3 down here.
Yes, I get my fire power back! Now, let's try to hang onto it this time!
It certainly wasn't to get a better view of a shell that was about to kill me.

Okay, at this point, the desynched Marina goes back and forth through this pipe on the overworld several times, and then eventually enters 2-A, where she just makes meaningless actions at the start of the level until the footage ends. It's nothing interesting, so I'll just cut it off here.
BLOCK FACTORYYY!!! Yeah, I thought I'd do that just to be silly here. However, I believe it's up to chance whether or not I can jump off of the green blocks now.
Over here, I timed my jumps properly to allow myself to ascend the continuously toggling blocks, courtesy of Mr. Koopa over there.
Yep, I kicked an ice block through the land, just like that.
Well, I'm stumped.

Well, I guess I'm going to have to go over 2-A with a fine-toothed comb (or something like that) in search of that missing star coin later. However, if any of you know where that star coin could be, let me know!
Huzzah!
Alright, moving along, it looks like we've got more ON/OFF action here.
Oh, what's this? Looks like we've got some of them frozen-types of blocks that break when fried. I'd better try to hang onto my fire power!
Well, the football became blatantly obvious when I took that dumb hit there!
Okay, let's try to do this right this time, because I'm running low on time!

Yep, there's-- Whoa, I can go back through this pipe?
Okay, that leads to 2-B, which is a red level. But, I'm not going to play that now. However, I am going to go back through 2-A at ludicrous speed to see if I can find that missing star coin...
Level makers, take note of this possible glitch, and be careful how you place your slopes.
Umm... What's going on? I don't remember acting like this... Oh, no... Don't tell me... ZSNES just desynched on me, didn't it?
Next up is more ON/OFF shenanigans. I progressed through this not-actually-very-complicated part like this.

Still eager for more pain and suffering?

Alright, so we've got a tide in effect here, just like with Mondo.
Huh. It's a two-way door for some reason, but that'll work just fine for resetting the escort mission.
Come on, if I can quickly shell jump to save my life, I should be able to shell jump over a simple wall like this when my life isn't in immediate danger.
Whoa! I nearly got booby-trapped there! However, if I scroll away and come back...
Yep, this is a definite desync. I did not get injured like this at all when I was actually playing (I'm amazed the desynched Marina picked up her reserve power up).
